      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is very important that you do not attempt to self-medicate or switch medications on your own, regardless of how busy your doctor is. St. John's Wort is not a benign substitute; combining it with SSRIs like sertraline is a known risk for dangerous side effects. If you cannot reach your primary physician, try calling your pharmacy to speak with a pharmacist, as they are experts in drug interactions and can offer immediate advice.",
